	<p>
		Welcome! I'm a researcher, educator, and technology enthusiast with a passion for understanding complex systems and making that knowledge accessible to others. My work sits at the intersection of data science, applied mathematics, and human-centred design — a combination that has led me to collaborate with institutions, startups, and research groups across multiple continents.
	</p>
	<p>
		Over the years I have developed skills spanning statistical modelling, machine learning, network analysis, and scientific computing. I also care deeply about the social dimensions of technology — how tools shape behaviour and what responsibilities come with building systems that affect people's lives. These questions drive my research agenda and inform the way I approach teaching.
	</p>
	<p>
		Outside of work I enjoy exploring new cities, experimenting in the kitchen, and volunteering with a community organisation focused on digital literacy. I am always open to new collaborations and conversations — do not hesitate to reach out.
	</p>

